, 
<materialsCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="516">“Los Cardones, sobre la Ruta Nacional N° 307, Kilometro 101, entre las localidades tucumanas de El Infi- ernillo y Amaicha del Valle, aproximada- mente a 2.500 metros sobre el nivel del mar (26°38 S-65°49° W),” Tucuman, Argentina</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[2080,2673,2348,2770]" pageId="5" pageNumber="516">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Contreras" authorityYear="1999" box="[2084,2322,2659,2692]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scagliai">Ctenomys scagliai</taxonomicName>
was classified as the Chacoan group, based on biogeographical data, but as belonging to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1848" box="[2576,2672,2737,2770]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opimus">opimus</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[1467,2671,2780,3477]" pageId="5" pageNumber="516">species group when considering molecular markers. Chromosomal complementis 2n = 36 and FN = 64, and sperm is symmetric. Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1469,2537,2854,2887]" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6588218" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6588218" box="[1469,2537,2854,2887]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6588218/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" targetBox="[1467,2057,2352,2766]" targetPageId="5">
